					<h1>Jobs at Jewelbots</h1>
					<h2>Software Developer</h2>
					<p class="small">
						Jewelbots is looking for a software developer to help us bring Jewelbots to life. As a software developer at Jewelbots, you will work as part of a team to:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>build our Social Media REST API for Jewelbots </li>
						<li>build out our Arduino tooling</li>
						<li>construct the Jewelbots community site</li>
						<li>launch our Ionic based iOS/Android app</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="small">
						You'll also be integral to shaping our culture and practices. You'll have the opportunity to help build the team you want to see. You'll also work on all facets of our software. We believe in open source software, and regularly open-source our projects as they ship. 
					</p>
					<p class="small">
						What we expect to see:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>solid programming skills and a record of getting stuff done</li>
						<li>interested in helping to bring technology to under-served segments of the market</li>
						<li>want to make software that is easy and fun to use</li>
						<li>believe in the collaborative process for software</li>
						<li>are willing to learn new technologies and platforms as needed to build new software</li>
						<li>have experience in one or more web server-side MVC frameworks</li>
						<li>proficiency in one or more languages, including JavaScript, C#, Python, Ruby</li>
					</ul>
					<h3>
						What we like to see (but not required):
					</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>open source experience, including any projects you've contributed to or any personal projects you're proud of</li>
						<li>experience shipping features using Test Driven Development</li>
						<li>proficiency with CSS</li>
						<li>experience with Angular and Amazon Web Services</li>
					</ul>
					<h3>
						Our stack:
					</h3>
					<p class="small">
						We believe in using the right tool for the job. We're currently working with node.js and Amazon Web Services for our web work, with C and gcc for our embedded work. 
					</p>
					<p class="small">
						Our preference is for developers based in either NYC or the Washington DC metro area, but we'll also accept remote applications as well. We want to find the right person for the job, no matter where you may be.
					</p>
					<h3>
						About Jewelbots
					</h3>
					<p class="small">
						Our goal is to make products that expose young girls to technology and make technology accessible to their interests. We want to build better software and have fun doing it. We believe strongly that diverse teams build better products.
